description:
@Fix existing bugs on our existing platform to make it more operational for the Moving and Transportation industry (moversfax.com). Working on Design and front/back end development as well
@U/I and U/X design and creative output is a must for the success of this position. We are looking for designers who are open to suggest different creative options to make the site more user friendly.for all members and organizers. 
@Offer option to corporate office for more interactive messaging system so customers and movers can interact better.
@Keep the corporate office aware of your progress by providing updated reports with tracking your design and web development features

We have other web related projects available as well in case this project doesn't seem to peak your interest. AS we have over 30 different projects available at the company, I am sure that one will fit your interest and experience.

As a Java Developer Intern, you will get experience working with end to end phases of the software development life cycle including technical research, requirements analysis, high level and technical design, improving user experience, shaping the face of our new products, building internal tools, implementation of enhancements to the product, unit testing, debugging, and maintenance.

Responsibilities:
◾  Identify issues and implement solutions to complex problems in large scale web platforms;
◾  Analyze & solve difficult problems across the stack;
◾  Work closely with operations and infrastructure to build high scale backend services;

Requirements:

◾  Software development experience;
◾  Strong application development knowledge of the following technologies:  Java, Scala, Docker, *MQ, Apache Kafka, Spark, Cassandra, PostgreSQL,  Python,  MySQL, Hive
◾  Experience designing, implementing and using web services in a Micro service Architecture;
◾  Familiar with relational & non-relational databases such as Postgres, Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL, DynamoFamiliar with CI (Continuous Integration) and CD (Continuous Delivery);

Good to have - Exposure to Big data technologies;
Nice to have - Experience with AWS;
Nice to have - Experience working in an agile development process.
